<br>
No big deal right? Then he showed me the book - his multi national corporation sent him through snail mail this week. I swear to god 200 pages of glossey shit about the evolution of his spectacular company.<br>
<br>
I came home tonight only to find awaiting in my mail box (postage paid) a beatiful printed glossey news magazine that would put Time, Newsweek or even National Geographic to shame. Telling me how well the company is doing and the great things we are doing for the environment (yeah right). <br>
<br>
Yah know, considering there are 50,000 employees in the US alone (in the business) and 6,000 retail locations are being closed, 300 IT individuals laid off and several thousand being laid off in the business (at least 1 per retail location logic would tell you). The company can afford to snail mail 50k Glossy news magazines? WTF that would have saved a number of jobs alone if they just put this shit on the corp intranet which they are already paying for!<br>
<br>
