My father is head of claims department for a subsidiary for Citigroup, I get some nice stories from time to time about the company and/or stupid policy holders.  If you work for Citigroup or any one of it's several subsidiaries, you don't have to worry about being laid off on Mondays or Fridays.  Monday they won't lay you off because heart attacks occur most often on Mondays.  Fridays they won't lay you off because then you have the whole weekend to dwell on it and either kill yourself or others.  All of this was implemented after they lost a few lawsuits to widows and family members.  So hey, if you work for Citigroup, they only days you have to worry are Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday!<br>
<br>
